Uses of Package
com.kuka.geometry.events

  • Packages that use com.kuka.geometry.events 
    Package Description
    com.kuka.geometry
    This package contains interfaces and classes for the KUKA scene graph and geometry model.
    com.kuka.geometry.events
    Contains classes of the KUKA scene graph event model.
    com.kuka.geometry.listeners
    This package contains interfaces for listeners that are notified on changes to the properties and to the hierarchy of objects and their owned frames.
  • Classes in com.kuka.geometry.events used by com.kuka.geometry 
    Class and Description
    PropertyEvent
    Event which indicates that the properties of objects or of their frames were changed within a monitored tree.
    TreeEvent
    Event which informs about changes to objects or their frames within a monitored tree.
  • Classes in com.kuka.geometry.events used by com.kuka.geometry.events 
    Class and Description
    FramePropertyEvent
    Event which indicates that the properties of an object frame within a monitored tree were changed.
    FrameStructureEvent
    Event which indicates that the structure of frames within a monitored tree was changed.
    ObjectPropertyEvent
    Event which indicates that the properties of an object within a monitored tree were changed.
    ObjectStructureEvent
    Event which indicates that the structure of objects within a monitored tree was changed.
    PropertyEvent
    Event which indicates that the properties of objects or of their frames were changed within a monitored tree.
    TreeEvent
    Event which informs about changes to objects or their frames within a monitored tree.
    TreeStructureEvent
    Event which indicates that the structure of a monitored tree was changed.
  • Classes in com.kuka.geometry.events used by com.kuka.geometry.listeners 
    Class and Description
    FrameConnectionEvent
    Event which indicates that the IFrameConnection of an object frame to its parent was changed.
    FrameCreateEvent
    Event which indicates that a frame was created on an object.
    FrameRemoveEvent
    Event which indicates that a frame was removed from an object.
    ObjectAttachEvent
    Event which indicates that an object was attached to another object.
    ObjectConnectionEvent
    Event which indicates that the ObjectConnection of an object, i.e. the connection from its parent, was changed.
    ObjectDetachEvent
    Event which indicates that an object was detached from another object.
    ObjectParameterEvent
    Event which indicates that the object parameters of an object were changed.
    PropertyEvent
    Event which indicates that the properties of objects or of their frames were changed within a monitored tree.
    RedundancyInformationEvent
    Event which indicates that the redundancy information of an ObjectFrame was changed.
